he novel Thirty-Six Hours) up to the final text version.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aFascismzEuropevFiction. 0aYoung menzEuropevFiction. 4aHorváth, Ödön von. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aHamminger, Julia.1 aKastberger, Klaus, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aReimann, Kerstin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVejvar, Martin.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2011z9783110261189oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2011z9783110261240oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311023803740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311025286640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110252866423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110252866/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2011  aZDB-23-DGGb2011  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014